column5: Hi. Alan here in Chicago. heading up to sioux narrows area on monday. just wondering if any one has been up there lately and can tell me how the water level is and the fishing has been. I know its always great but I just have to ask. Going to the snake bay area. thanks a lot alan

also check out Shore Island area a bit to the west and north. some great action. Saw some posts about it at http://justfishontario.com/disc54_toc.htm Seems this area holds about every kind of structure and is good early and late in the year especially.
frozen on the 12th of september 6 yrs ago?
Can anyone tell me if the bridge in Sioux Narrows is finished? Somethings take forever.
You better be careful, just talked to some friends who live on Snake Bay and there is a ton of slush on the lake right now make travel a little crazy. BOB
There's a couple more feet of snow right now than at this time most years. The water level will be up this spring.
